data.name: lblModule.HelpText
data.value: Select this if you want CallButler to run an add-on module.

data.name: lblScript.HelpText
data.value:
Use this if you want to run a custom-built script after the personalized greeting is played. With a custom script you can create your own call flows and even interface with databases and other applications.
To create a custom script you may want to use the inTeliScript editor included with CallButler. See the CallButler documentation for information on creating and using custom scripts.

data.name: lblScript.Text
data.value: Run a custom script (For advanced users)

data.name: lblHangUp.HelpText
data.value:
Select this if you want to hang up on this specific caller after the personalized message is played.
You might use this personalization option to:
- Notify unwanted callers that you will not take their calls

data.name: lblTransfer.HelpText
data.value:
Select this if you want this specific caller to be transferred directly to an extension after the personalized greeting is played.
You might use this personalization option to:
- Transfer important callers directly to the company owner - Transfer customers directly to their personal account reps

data.name: lblTransfer.HelpTitle
data.value: Transfer the Call to an Extension

data.name: lblTransfer.Text
data.value: Transfer the call to an extension

data.name: lblContinueCall.HelpText
data.value:
Select this if you want this specific caller to continue with the call as any other caller would (ie, after the personalized greeting is played, the caller will be sent to the main menu).
You might use this personalization option to:
- Tell callers in a specific area about an upcoming event

data.name: lblContinueCall.HelpTitle
data.value: Continue with the Call as Normal

data.name: lblContinueCall.Text
data.value: Continue with the call as normal

data.name: smoothLabel3.HelpText
data.value:
Specify a path to a custom script file. CallButler will execute this custom script after the personalized greeting has been played.
Please note that if you are managing a CallButler service on another computer, you will need to specify a path to a script that is saved on that computer.

data.name: label4.Text
data.value: After the personalized message is played...

data.name: wizardHeader2.Description
data.value: Please specify a personalized message to be played for this caller.

data.name: smoothLabel5.HelpText
data.value:
Specify a value here if you have multiple inbound telephone numbers and want CallButler to inspect the dialed telephone number.
You can use the * character for wildcard matching. For example if you wanted to match all numbers in area code 206, you would specify a value of "1206*" or "*206*" (without the quotes).
Note: For CallButler for Skype editions, this number may also be a Skype Name.

data.name: smoothLabel4.HelpText
data.value:
You may choose to specify a single value for Caller ID / Name, Caller Telephone Number and Dialed Telephone Number or you may choose to provide a value for all of them.
For example if you wanted to match all callers that begin with J, you would enter "J*" for Caller ID / Name and leave Caller Telephone Number blank.
If you wanted to match all callers that begin with J AND are in the 206 area code, you would enter "J*" for CallerID / Name and "*206*" for Caller Telephone Number.

data.name: smoothLabel4.HelpTitle
data.value: Caller ID / Name and Telephone NUmber

data.name: smoothLabel2.HelpText
data.value: Use this space to comment on this Call Personalization. This is used for your reference only and will not affect the operation of this Call Personalization.

data.name: lblOneTime.HelpText
data.value: If you select this box, CallButler will only use this Call Personalization for the first time this person calls.

data.name: lblRegex.HelpText
data.value:
With regular expressions you can create very complex matching algorithms. Check this box if you would like CallButler to interpret the values used for Caller ID and Telephone Number as regular expressions.
If you are unfamiliar with regular expressions you will find numerous sources for documentation and tutorials on the web.

data.name: lblRegex.Text
data.value: Use regular expressions for matching (For advanced users)

data.name: smoothLabel1.HelpText
data.value:
Specify a value here if you want CallButler to inspect the telephone number of the caller to determine if or how it should personalize the call.
You can use the * character for wildcard matching. For example if you wanted to match all callers in area code 206, you would specify a value of "1206*" or "*206*" (without the quotes).
Note: For CallButler for Skype editions, this number may also be a Skype Name.

data.name: lblCallerID.HelpText
data.value:
Specify a value here if you want CallButler to inspect the Caller ID or name of the caller to determine if or how it should personalize the call.
You can use the * character for wildcard matching. For example if you wanted to match all callers with a name that start with the letter J, you would specify a value of "J*" (without the quotes).
Note: For CallButler for Skype users you may specify a Skype Name for this value.
